ext_descriptions.ext_description:
The text that specifies the meaning of the relationship.
Where applicable, the following values shall be used:
'decomposition': The related breakdown_element_select is one of potentially more components of the relating complex_product_select. This relation type shall only be used for complex_product_select and breakdown_element_select of the same type;
'functionality': The related breakdown_element_select is an element of the functional structure of the relating complex_product_select. This relation type shall only be used with a complex_product_select of type Alternative_solution or Physical_element_definition and with a breakdown_element_select of type Functional_element_definition ;
The functional element 'heat dissipation' may be considered as one of the functionalities to be fulfilled by any technical solution for the physical element 'braking system'.
'occurrence': The related breakdown_element_select is an occurrence defined by the relating complex_product_select. This relation type shall only be used if related breakdown_element_select is of type physical element;
'realization': The related breakdown_element_select is a means for fulfilling, either partially or fully, the requirements identified with the relating complex_product_select. This relation type shall be used only when the complex_product_select and the breakdown_element_select are of different types ;
The physical element 'braking system' may be considered as a means to realize the functional element 'braking'.
'specialization': The related breakdown_element_select fulfils the requirements of the relating complex_product_select in a more specific way than defined for the relating complex_product_select. This relation type shall only be used for breakdown_element_select and complex_product_select of the same type.
